@Peter C.

“ details, considerations, or pieces of information of little importance or value”

Glad you found none, and enjoyed the puzzle. To me, it was omnipresent.

@Deb Amlen
To quote Sam Corbin's recent response: "Make my day, why don’t you!!"
There are days, Ms. Deb...

@Jerry

You know that I don't hold off invading this forum with my prolixity.  Neither should you.

Best of luck.

@MmmmHmm I’ve read a couple meh responses in Wordplay, but generally you’re right—the columnists have lots of enthusiasm for the puzzles. 

To be fair, though, these are the small percentage of submitted puzzles that were deemed good enough to be accepted, and which were then revised multiple times by the constructor and the editing team before reaching our screens. 

Which is just to say, there’s probably something worthy of my enthusiasm even in my least favorite puzzle. And yeah, something worthy of a yawn as well, I suppose, but I’d personally rather Wordplay continue to focus on the former.
